---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Travel guides and photography from real experience — built to help you explore smarter."
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <div class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-hero__inner">
        <div class="about-hero__photo">
          <img
            src="/images/bradon-about.jpg"
            alt="Bradon — writer and photographer behind Globe & Frame"
            width="960"
            height="640"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="about-hero__body">
          <p class="about-hero__eyebrow">Globe &amp; Frame</p>
          <h1 class="about-hero__name">Hi, I'm Bradon.</h1>
          <p class="about-hero__sub">New York City · 30+ countries · always chasing the next adventure and 75+ long-haul flights</p>
          <p class="about-hero__intro">
            I live in New York City with my faithful German Shorthair Pointer, Daisy. I find just as much joy in
            cooking at home as I do in dining out. Exploring cities, beaches, photography, paddle boarding, skiing,
            and uncovering excellent Italian cuisine are some of my favorite pastimes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-facts">
        <div class="about-fact">
          <div class="about-fact__label">Based in</div>
          <div class="about-fact__value">New York City</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fact">
          <div class="about-fact__label">Countries visited</div>
          <div class="about-fact__value">30+ and counting</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fact">
          <div class="about-fact__label">Travel style</div>
          <div class="about-fact__value">Beer to rosé</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fact">
          <div class="about-fact__label">Co-pilot</div>
          <div class="about-fact__value">Daisy, GSP</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fact">
          <div class="about-fact__label">Best meal</div>
          <div class="about-fact__value">Italian, anywhere</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="article-prose">
        <h2>Why Travel</h2>
        <p>
          Travel has a way of opening your eyes to new cultures, new cuisines, and new perspectives. It is why I
          always encourage friends and family to go see the world for themselves.
        </p>
        <p>
          We all share one planet, but the best way to truly understand it is by experiencing it firsthand. That is
          why I write, photograph, and share my experiences — to pass along what I have learned and help others travel
          smarter, discover incredible destinations, and feel more confident exploring the world.
        </p>

        <h2>The Travel Style</h2>
        <p>In summing up my travel style...</p>
        <div class="pull-quote">
          I can savor a beer in the Redneck Riviera just as much as a glass of rose in the French Riviera. My
          blog embodies a certain <em>je ne sais quoi</em>.
        </div>

        <h2>Where I Have Been</h2>
        <p>
          Over the years, I have traveled across a range of destinations, learning what actually makes a place
          memorable to me. It is rarely just what you see — it is how you experience it, from the meals and moments
          to the people you meet along the way.
        </p>
        <p>
          From iconic cities to smaller destinations that surprised me along the way, every trip has added another
          layer to how I explore, write, and share what is worth experiencing.
        </p>
        <a class="article-link" href="/city-guides/">Explore the City Guides</a>

        <h2>Where I'm Dreaming About</h2>
        <p>
          There are still plenty of places I am excited to experience next. Some destinations stand out for their
          food, landscapes, culture, design, or simply the feeling I imagine they leave behind.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some are already on the calendar. Others are still further out, part of a longer list of places I want to
          experience the right way.
        </p>
        <a class="article-link" href="/elevate-your-travel/where-i-am-dreaming/">See What's Inspiring Me</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="dreaming-cta">
      <div class="container dreaming-cta__inner">
        <div>
          <h3>Want to go somewhere together?</h3>
          <p>
            Tell me where you want to go and I'll help you build a plan around the experience you're looking for.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a class="button button--primary" href="/custom-inquiry/">Plan a Custom Trip</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
